\begin{align*}
V_{\text{shaded}} &= V_{\text{larger sphere}} - V_{\text{smaller sphere}} \\
&= \frac{4}{3} \pi (25)^3 - \frac{4}{3} \pi (17)^3 \\
&= \frac{4}{3} \pi (15625 - 4913) \\
&= \frac{4}{3} \pi (10712) \\
&= \frac{42848}{3} \pi
\end{align*}

Since the third sphere will have a volume equal to that of the shaded region, we can set up the equation:

\begin{align*}
\frac{4}{3} \pi r^3 &= \frac{42848}{3} \pi \\
r^3 &= \frac{42848}{4} \\
r^3 &= 10712 \\
r &= \sqrt[3]{10712} \\
r &= \boxed{22\sqrt[3]{2}}
\end{align*}

For the expression to be defined, both the numerator and denominator must be real numbers. The expressions inside each square root must be non-negative:
\begin{align*}
x-2 &\ge 0\\
