\begin{align*}
5-x &\ge 0\\
5 &\ge x\\
x &\le 5
\end{align*}

Combining the two conditions, we find that $2 \le x \le 5$. However, the denominator cannot equal zero, so $5 - x > 0 \Rightarrow x < 5$.

Therefore, the domain of the expression is $\boxed{[2, 5)}$

